FROM devstral:24b

# ─── Context & Batching ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Claude Code requires a large context window for agentic tasks (file trees,
# multi-file edits, long tool call chains). 64k is the recommended minimum.
# Matches the capacity of the devstral-24b-64k variant.
PARAMETER num_ctx 65536

# Number of tokens processed in parallel during the prefill phase.
# 1024 is a good balance between throughput and memory pressure on Apple Silicon.
# Lower this (e.g. 512) if you see memory spikes on large context loads.
PARAMETER num_batch 1024

# Physical performance cores on the M5 Pro. Leaving 2 free for the OS and
# Ollama's management threads avoids thermal throttling during long sessions.
PARAMETER num_thread 12

# ─── Sampling ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Fully deterministic output. Critical for Claude Code — tool call XML/JSON
# must be well-formed and reproducible. Any value above 0 risks malformed
# responses that Claude Code interprets as model errors.
PARAMETER temperature 0.0

# Nucleus sampling threshold. At temperature 0.0 this has no practical effect,
# but kept here as a sane default if you ever bump temperature for experiments.
PARAMETER top_p 0.9

# No repetition penalty. A value above 1.0 can penalize legitimate re-use of
# keywords, variable names, or structural patterns in generated code.
PARAMETER repeat_penalty 1.0

# ─── Stop Tokens ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Mistral-family control tokens only. Devstral is built on Mistral-Small-3.1
# and uses [INST]/[/INST] delimiters — NOT <|user|>/<|assistant|> (those are
# Zephyr/Phi-style and will cause silent template mismatches).
PARAMETER stop "[INST]"
PARAMETER stop "[/INST]"
PARAMETER stop "<|endoftext|>"

# ─── Template ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# DO NOT add a TEMPLATE block here. The devstral:24b Ollama image ships with
# the correct mistral-common chat template built in. Overriding it with a
# custom template (even a plausible-looking one) breaks tool calling and
# function call formatting that Claude Code depends on.
